Different types of build triggers?

1. Build Periodically
2. GitHub Hook Trigger
3. Poll SCM
4. Build After Other Projects


Jenkins Build Triggers – Simple Interview Answer
1. Build Periodically
Like a alarm clock – builds at a fixed time, no matter what.

"Run every night at 2 AM" — good for nightly reports or cleanup jobs.


2. GitHub Hook Trigger - Then in GitHub → Repo Settings → Webhooks add:
http://jenkinsip:8080/github-webhook/

Instant build on push. Best & most common for GitHub projects.


3. Poll SCM
Like checking your phone every 5 mins for new messages instead of waiting for a notification.

Jenkins keeps asking GitHub "anything new?" — works but wastes resources.


4. Build After Other Projects
Like a relay race – one job finishes, the next one starts automatically.

Used to chain jobs: Build → Test → Deploy.



