Snyk checks online database
      ↓
"This library has CVE-2021-1234 vulnerability!"
      ↓
Suggests: upgrade to spring-boot 2.7.0

Snyk looks at your libraries/packages — not your code!



SonarQube → scans YOUR CODE


Your Application.java has:
String query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE id=" + userId;
      ↓
SonarQube detects
      ↓
"SQL Injection vulnerability in line 45!"
      ↓
Developer must fix the code


SonarQube looks at your actual code — not libraries!


Simple analogy:

Your Car:
Snyk       → checks if spare parts are faulty    (libraries)
SonarQube  → checks if engine is built correctly  (your code)


In real companies — both are used:

Snyk      → "your libraries are safe" ✅
SonarQube → "your code is clean" ✅
Both pass → pipeline continues 🚀

|       | Snyk                    | SonarQube                |
| ----- | ----------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Scans | pom.xml dependencies    | Your Java code           |
| Finds | Vulnerable libraries    | SQL injection, XSS, bugs |
| Fixes | Upgrade library version | Fix your code            |
| Type  | Dependency scanning     | Static code analysis     |


