Types of Nodes:

Jenkins Master (Controller)
      ↓
├── Master Node    → manages Jenkins, schedules jobs
└── Agent Nodes    → actually runs the pipeline/jobs

Master Node:

✅ Manages Jenkins UI
✅ Schedules builds
✅ Stores configurations
✅ Distributes jobs to agents
❌ Should NOT run builds (bad practice)

Agent Node:

✅ Actually runs the pipeline
✅ Can be Linux, Windows, Mac
✅ Multiple agents = parallel builds
✅ Can have different tools installed

In your Jenkinsfile:

agent any              // any available node
agent none             // no default agent
agent { label 'linux'} // specific node with label
agent { docker 'maven'}// run inside docker container


Why multiple nodes:

Master
  ├── Agent 1 (Linux)   → runs Java builds
  ├── Agent 2 (Windows) → runs .NET builds
  └── Agent 3 (Linux)   → runs Python builds

3 jobs can run SIMULTANEOUSLY! 🚀


